[SN]TITLE[SN]
M4 Briton Ferry Bridge reopens at Neath Port Talbot

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The M4 Briton Ferry Bridge at Neath Port Talbot has reopened following a police incident on Thursday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Motorists faced delays as emergency services dealt with the incident between junction 41 for Baglan and junction 42 for Fabian Way.
It happened on the westbound side of the bridge.
A diversion was in place on the A48 Old Briton Ferry Bridge.
